description.0: Prison-break, Wolverine style! But can even Logan escape the clutches of the cosmic being known as the Collector?
description.3: The Hulk learns the ultimate truth about his life, just in time to clash once more with the Abomination! And even if he wins that fight, he'll have a reckoning with his oldest and most persistent nemesis - Thunderbolt Ross!
description.4: The first appearance of Yelena Belova.  Tensions continue to rise as the human forces marshaled outside the city of Attilan discover a weakness in the energy shields.  How will the Inhumans respond?
description.5: J2 may have found a kindred spirit in 'hero' Magneta- that is, if they can stop attacking each other first! Who is the woman modeling herself after the Master of Magnetism? And why does she consider J2 a teammate? Wild Thing stars in her own adventure!
description.8: Fabian Cortez has an army at his disposable...and he's far from afraid to use it.
description.10: Iron Man poses the age-old question: is Cap's shield really unbreakable?
description.11: Introducing...LADYHAWK! Spider-Girl meets the lovely yet lethal crime fighter.
description.12: Magneto has an ultimatum for the United Nations - a haven for mutants or total destruction.
description.13: While the X-Men battle the Acolytes, the government tries to destroy Magneto before he can destroy them! Plus, the origin of Joseph!
description.15: The Fantastic Four's battle with Ronan the Accuser rages on! But as their chances grow more and more dire, Reed must call on another scientific genius to help save the day - the invincible IRON MAN!
description.17: Argos the Almighty comes from the greatest of bloodlines; he is the son Hercules, after all!
description.18: The New Hellions are here and they are recruiting! Will any of X-Force join them? Or are we headed towards a battle royale between the two teams?
description.19: Iron Man joins the Fantastic Four in their search for the Invisible Woman- and both parties soon discover that Sue's been enslaved by Ronan the Accuser!
description.25: While Cable’s taking down one of the Tinkerer's androids, Rachel Summers makes her mighty return!
description.26: The all-new Spider-Man revealed! The enigmatic Ritual of the Five has bestowed spider-powers onto a worthy vessel. But just how worthy a vessel is a question Peter Parker's asking! Is this new Spidey an imposter...or an inspiration?
description.29: As'Boba Fett'hones in on his quarry, he is followed by'Darth Vader's hired goons, but the Dark Lord trusts no one in this particular endeavor, nor does he expect any of them to walk away once the prize is his. But Boba Fett knows the craft of tracking, and he also knows that if Vader wants something this badly, it must be very precious indeed!
description.30: Trapped on PRISON WORLD! Light years from home with no way out, Logan's only option is to fight for his life!
description.31: With the destruction of the Death Star, the Rebel Alliance has struck a critical blow against the forces of the evil Emperor Palpatine. And with the Senate dissolved and the Empire's main tool of domination reduced to space dust, thousands of systems have joined their voices against the Empire. After Darth Vader's narrow escape from the doomed Death Star, the dark lord is consumed with a desire to find the identity of the Force-strong young pilot, who had fired the fatal shot. For the young pilot represents the strength and tenacity of this newly galvanized Rebel Alliance, and perhaps, for Vader, he represents much, much more...
description.32: As'Ki-Adi-Mundi'gets closer to the truth of who is seeking to destabilize his homeworld, and why, he comes closer and closer to his own doom, and only the dimly remembered teachings of his'diminutive Jedi Master'can save him!
description.33: Magneto uses an innocent life as a bargaining tool against humanity.
description.36: The pieces of the mystery are slowly coming together as'Kir Kanos'races towards the'Zanibar'homeworld,'Xo, in an attempt to save'Mirith Sinn'from a fate worse than death. But will he be in time? Will personal animosities between the two be too great? Meanwhile,'Grappa'the'Hutt'finds himself in an awkward situation, with the heat of the'Black Sun'starting to make him sweat.
description.41: WOLVERINE VS. THE MARVEL UNIVERSE! Featuring too many guest stars to name!
description.42: Mara Jade'has destroyed many enemies of the'Empire'in her time, and has always carried out her missions with forethought and skill. But an unforeseen variable is about to enter the scene of her final mission for'her dead employer, and Mara knows that her own survival is second to getting the job done!
description.44: A creator’s sneak peek at Gambit’s 1999 ongoing! Join writer Fabian Nicieza as he gives you the lowdown on everyone’s favorite Cajun scoundrel! With exclusive artist’s material by Steve Skroce, and a who’s who gallery of Gambit’s friends, foes, and femmes!
description.47: In the ultimate final battle, Adam Warlock stands alone against Syphonn, Annihilus, and Blastaar!
description.48: Hulk and Qnax continue their search for the Ultimate Machine, and come face to face with the most mysterious character in all of Marvel - the Watcher! Plus, the shocking secrets of Betty Ross' death are at last revealed!
description.49: The situation in Attilan grows more complicated as Namor claims the island as land belonging to his kingdom.
description.50: Who is Wild Thing, and what beef does she have with J2? The daughter of Wolverine pounces and Zane is left entirely unawares! Sachi Yama continues to unravel the mystery of the new Juggernaut, endangering not only herself...but her son too!
description.51: Spider-Man and Thor fight in the streets of New York City, but the clock is ticking because Aunt May is in dire need of help!
description.54: Take a look inside one of the most evil minds in the Marvel Universe. Red Skull is back!
description.55: VENOM IS BACK! And this time it's Spider-Girl who must save Spider-Man!
description.56: What is haunting Colossus and what does it have to do with his sister Illyana?
description.59: Ronan has fought the Fantastic Four to a standstill, and now he holds Sue and Johnny Storm captive on the Moon! Can Reed and Ben possibly succeed where the whole team together failed!?
description.61: We'll see if the newly assembled Avengers are up to the task of taking on a real super-villain. Enter...Doctor Doom!
description.62: Introducing the New Hellions! What is this new team's goal and what does this mean for X-Force?
description.63: An all-new Baron Blood rises as the Baroness' vampires come into contact with the Grail! Joey Chapman may not have been a great actor, but will he step up to the plate in his role as Union Jack? Should he fail, London will fall!
description.64: What happens when the Thunderbolts have a night off? The team tries to unwind for some much needed R&R, but find that fate has other plans! Check out what the T-bolt members do, or destroy, in their downtime in this special spotlight issue!
description.65: All is not as it seems at Dr. Basel's Stress Clinic- especially when Rumiko witnesses Tony being brainwashed in his sleep!
description.66: Does New York City have an all-new Spider-Man? It sure seems that way, given that Peter Parker's retired the red and blue. But who is this new 'hero' masquerading as the original wall-crawler? And will the villain Shadrac call Peter into action once more?
description.68: Read journalist Irene Merryweather’s full history on Cable! Will her revelations answer questions about Cable’s past that he himself doesn’t know?
description.71: Ki-Adi-Mundi,'Jedi Knight'of the planet'Cerea, has been charged with murder, and only the high technology of the'Republic'can exonerate him. But this isn't the most brutal irony; Ki's own teenage daughter is an accessory to the murder! Sinister forces are gathering around Cerea, but what could they possibly want with a remote, low-tech farm world?
description.72: Before the events of'A New Hope,'Darth Vader'employed'the galaxy's greatest'bounty hunter'on a search-and-retrieval mission:'Boba Fett'must discover and return to Vader a single small box, the contents of which could change the fate of the galaxy. For such an important mission, Vader cannot rely on a single operative, nor can he allow that operative to walk away alive!
description.73: Kyp Durron'thought he had destroyed the'Leviathan'that laid waste to the mining colony of'Corbos. But he was wrong. He killed its offspring and now the mother of the Leviathan is looking to take revenge on the'Jedi. Now Kyp and the rest of the'Jedi Academy'must face a threat even larger than they had first imagined.
description.75: The Cerebros continue their attempt to catalog mutants, but the X-Men are determined to put an end to it all.
description.76: While'Grappa's pirates turn up the heat on the'Rebel'cargo routes, the Interim Council'sinks to unprecedented depths under the leadership of Xandel Carivus.'Mirith Sinn'finds herself the victim of the greatest deception of all when an old comrade finds her amidst Grappa's thugs. Meanwhile, what has'Kir Kanos'gotten himself to?
description.79: A night at the bar turns ugly! Logan has to face off with an unstable mutant powerhouse, and even he might be in over his head! Good thing he's got help from Carol Danvers, a.k.a. WARBIRD!
description.84: The Iron Man armor is killing Tony Stark! Tony's staff sends him to the Basel Stress Clinic...and the consequences are dangerous.
description.85: Collects The 'Nam #1-10.  Don't worry about choosing sides, because this far into the heart of darkness, things get pretty gray. Follow Private Ed Marks and his fellow soldiers through a jungle of blood, lies, betrayal and valor. It's the war that defined a generation, where the heroes may not be super, but they're all too human.
description.87: Exodus returns...but what does he want with the X-Men?
description.94: The Hulk is enlisted by a mysterious alien known as Qnax to help him retrieve a powerful machine - and whisked away to another world! Meanwhile, General Ross' dogged search for the Hulk continues as always, but he encounters a completely different gamma-powered beast than he expected!
description.95: A startling truth is revealed to Black Bolt about the nature of Terrigenesis. Everything the Inhumans thought they knew about their society was wrong.
description.96: Zane delves deep into his subconscious to uncover his fears about his father Juggernaut. But the psychotherapy goes a little too far when J2 must confront Juggernaut in the flesh! Will this father-son reunion have a happy ending? Introducing Slippery Sam!

0.text: Prison-break, Wolverine style! But can even Logan escape the clutches of the cosmic being known as the Collector?

1.text: The time-displaced Avengers...are displaced once more!  The team is split up in an apocalyptic future, the Wild West and 1959!
The time-displaced Avengers...are displaced once more!  The team is split up in an apocalyptic future, the Wild West and 1959!

2.text: Issue "O". Machine Man is summoned by Uatu to witness...Earth X!  What happened to the Marvel Universe that lead to this dystopian future?

6.text: From the skyscraping heights of Manhattan buildings…to the city’s underground! Spidey and Bobby Drake, otherwise known as ICEMAN, team up in a chilling new battle.

7.text: Spider-Man faces a challenge few ever escape from…Mysterio's expert hypnosis!

9.text: Mephisto takes Black Panther and Everett Ross to Hell! The demon exploits T’Challa’s vulnerability to the Wakandan people. Will Mephisto burn Panther to a crisp with mind games?

14.text: The return of the mysterious Citizen V! But is he here to lead the Thunderbolts- or to take them down? That's the question Hawkeye has to answer as the T-Bolts square off once again against the Masters of Evil! Two fights have ended with mixed results- who will win this final grudge match showdown?

16.text: Murdock's mother is in danger and so Daredevil races to her rescue! This issue features Doctor Strange, Mephisto, Bullseye, and the death of someone close to Matt!
Murdock's mother is in danger and so Daredevil races to her rescue! This issue features Doctor Strange, Mephisto, Bullseye, and the death of someone close to Matt!

20.text: Guest-starring Storm! Gambit and ‘Stormy’ travel to Muir Island to test the outer limits of Remy’s newfound abilities. But in true ragin’ Cajun fashion, Gambit’s also there for a heist! Will Moira MacTaggert’s research be safe from his sticky fingers?

21.text: Captain America finds himself in the infancy of his country in 1781, an era when the United States threatened to implode! Is post-Colonial America ready for Cap’s kind of heroism?

22.text: The Flight of Bones continues! As the trail of mystical clues grows hotter, dark secrets are revealed that will shake even the Sorcerer Supreme to his core!

23.text: Story continued from Heroes Reborn: Heroes the Return #4. One year ago the greatest heroes in the Marvel Universe, the Avengers and Fantastic Four, fought the mutant menace known as Onslaught and were sucked into an alternate universe. They escaped. However, the Odinson and the nefarious Victor Von Doom did not make the trip home. At least at first. This is the tale of the secret odyssey of Thor and Doctor Doom. It is a tale of bravery, sacrifice, and ultimately...betrayal.

24.text: The Brute…on trial for the deaths of Man-Spider and the Green Goblin!

25.text: While Cable’s taking down one of the Tinkerer's androids, Rachel Summers makes her mighty return!

27.text: Spider-Man must contend with the Lizard in the Everglades!

30.text: Trapped on PRISON WORLD! Light years from home with no way out, Logan's only option is to fight for his life!

34.text: Deadpool must embrace his destiny in order to defeat the extraterrestrial Destroyer.

35.text: It's the Avengers vs Immortus' invading army.  But what is Immortus after that will change the timestream permanently?
It's the Avengers vs Immortus' invading army.  But what is Immortus after that will change the timestream permanently?

37.text: Justice and Firestar are torn between new allegiances and old as they face the diabolical forces of A.I.M. alongside the Avengers. Guest-starring the New Warriors!

39.text: During Tokkots' villainous rampage in Midtown, Thor's hammer fails him yet again! Even with Spider-Man by his side, will Thor be able to take Tokkots down?

41.text: WOLVERINE VS. THE MARVEL UNIVERSE! Featuring too many guest stars to name!

43.text: Gambit plays his cards right and vaults into his own kinetically charged solo adventures! He's a lover and a thief, but what else does ragin' Cajun Remy LeBeau get up to when he isn't hangin' wit' de X-Men? Would you believe raiding lost temples of Doom? Clashing with the deadly X-Cutioner? Or teaming up with Sabretooth? Still, there's always time for the ladies- like old friend Storm and his favorite cherie, Rogue. But who is Gambit's gaseous green guardian?

44.text: A creator’s sneak peek at Gambit’s 1999 ongoing! Join writer Fabian Nicieza as he gives you the lowdown on everyone’s favorite Cajun scoundrel! With exclusive artist’s material by Steve Skroce, and a who’s who gallery of Gambit’s friends, foes, and femmes!

45.text: Three never-before-told tales of suspense from Cap’s incredible career!

46.text: The latest in the Marvel Knights series takes a bold new look at Marvel's Sorcerer Supreme! A series of bizarre robberies and a spate of spontaneous combustions set Stephen on the trail of an old enemy, and he'll have to employ all his skill to discover the answers! Magic meets noir in an atmospheric Strange tale!

47.text: In the ultimate final battle, Adam Warlock stands alone against Syphonn, Annihilus, and Blastaar!

52.text: Once thought to be dead, Spider-Man attempts to save J. Jonah Jameson from the wrath of Mysterio. This will be far from an easy task.

53.text: Black Panther must face Hatut Zeraze! Everett Ross makes some startling revelations. Then, Panther's final confrontation with Mephisto. Can the battered T’Challa manage to defeat two foes? Or will the demon Mephisto drag him to hell?

57.text: THE HUNT FOR XAVIER CONCLUSION Will young Nina be able to reprogram Cerebro? And what should happen is she fails? Professor Xavier is found, and recounts his dream for mutantkind to a sentient, and errant, Cerebro.

58.text: After a battle with the Avengers, the Thunderbolts' leader steps down, but who will take their place? There is one candidate, but it won't go over well with the rest of the team…

60.text: Matt Murdock's mother reveals herself to her son! Can this rendezvous help to clear Matt's head or will it just stir things up again? Plus, Bullseye has been hired to retrieve the child!
Matt Murdock's mother reveals herself to her son! Can this rendezvous help to clear Matt's head or will it just stir things up again? Plus, Bullseye has been hired to retrieve the child!

64.text: What happens when the Thunderbolts have a night off? The team tries to unwind for some much needed R&R, but find that fate has other plans! Check out what the T-bolt members do, or destroy, in their downtime in this special spotlight issue!

67.text: Spider-Man faces off with Doc Ock, with a little confidence boost from Johnny Storm, aka the Human Torch! Plus, Flash Thompson is kidnapped by Dr. Doom!

68.text: Read journalist Irene Merryweather’s full history on Cable! Will her revelations answer questions about Cable’s past that he himself doesn’t know?

69.text: It's your friendly neighborhood Man-Spider, complete with extra arms! But can the The Six help the hero tackle the Green Goblin before things get deadly?

70.text: The final battle between Heaven and Hell is waged! Olivier and his demonic horde give Punisher and his angel allies a holy crusade they'll never forget!

77.text: Tiamat goes on a killing spree as a wounded Deadpool regroups and regenerates.

78.text: Rick Jones holds the key to stopping the time-war, but can the Avengers trust Kang...or even each other?
Rick Jones holds the key to stopping the time-war, but can the Avengers trust Kang...or even each other?

79.text: A night at the bar turns ugly! Logan has to face off with an unstable mutant powerhouse, and even he might be in over his head! Good thing he's got help from Carol Danvers, a.k.a. WARBIRD!

82.text: Hercules and Thor head to Mount Olympus, home of the Greek Pantheon, to ask Zeus for help. A dark enemy is mustering its forces and the Gods will need all the help they can get!

83.text: Kicking off the Amazing Spider-Man’s second ongoing series! And the dynamic duo of writer Howard Mackie and artist John Byrne start things off with a bang…and a question- where the heck is Spider-Man? The super hero world is distinctly lacking a certain wall-crawler. Will the FF’s Human Torch solve the mystery of a Spider gone AWOL?

86.text: Spider-Man may be able to take on the Vulture, but what happens when the Tinkerer enter the fray?

87.text: Exodus returns...but what does he want with the X-Men?

88.text: Iron Man takes on the Sons of Yinsen in Japan!

89.text: Can Havok prevent Madelyne Pryor from becoming the Goblin Queen and save her son Scotty?

90.text: The Goblin Queen has turned The Six on Havok and he'll need the help of as many Avengers as he can find to stop them!

91.text: Series finale to this horror-suspense thriller! This is it! The STAKES have never been higher as Blade takes on the monstrous Yves St. Monroe!

92.text: Punisher is dragged further into hell after being taken to Olivier's base of operations!

93.text: Flashback special! An acting company “plays” out the formative trauma from Bruce Banner’s childhood…the death of his mother by his father’s hands. Forgiveness meets a brutal end in this gut punch issue!

97.text: Shortly after hanging up the web-shooters for good, Peter Parker encounters a new and different Spider-MAN!

98.text: See Spidey wear a rarely seen costume all the way back from 1999! We begin with one of Spider-Man's main nemeses, Mysterio, blaming Spider-Man for the killing of J. Jonah Jameson. Where will this amazing series go from here?

99.text: The origin of Achebe revealed! While Mephisto bides time with Everett Ross, Black Panther concludes his investigation. How will T’Challa bring the murderer to justice?
